==English==

===Noun===
'''phal'''

# An extremely hot [[curry]]. The name was made up by British [[restaurateur]]s and the [[dish]] is simply any standard [[curry]] with insane amounts of chili added.
#: ''I've drunk ten pints of [[lager]] and now I'm having a phal before I down the next ten''


===Adjective===
'''phal'''

# A [[qualifier]] placed after the name of an [[ingredient]] to from the name of an insanely hot [[curry]].
#:''There's nothing better after ten pints of [[lager]] than a nice chicken phal''